f%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20has%20been%20the%20marginal%20role%20played%20by%20Russian%20airpower.%20Expectations%20that%20Russian%20fighters%20and%20bombers%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffighting-in-ukraine-reveals-russian-air-force-fragility-think-tank-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblast%20a%20path%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20ground%20troops%20%E2%80%94%20as%20US%20airpower%20did%20in%20Desert%20Storm%20%E2%80%94%20were%20disappointed.%20Instead%2C%20Ukrainian%20anti-aircraft%20missiles%20have%20kept%20Russia's%20air%20force%20at%20bay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Russia%20has%20hit%20on%20a%20way%20for%20its%20air%20force%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20the%20VKS%20%E2%80%94%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20while%20staying%20away%20from%20the%20battlefield%20%E2%80%94%20massive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-glide-bomb-strikes-on-ukraine-decreased-still-major-threat-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglide%20bombing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20that%20approach%20seems%20to%20be%20successful%20enough%20that%20a%20British%20think%20tank%20is%20calling%20for%20NATO%20air%20forces%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGlide%20bombs%20gave%20the%20VKS%20teeth%20without%20the%20need%20to%20first%20achieve%20air%20superiority%20or%20gain%20the%20ability%20to%20penetrate%20Ukrainian%20airspace%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20analysts%20Jack%20Watling%20and%20Nick%20Reynolds%20in%20a%20report%20for%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20British%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20Russia's%20airpower%20woes%20have%20become%20NATO's%20worries.%20Since%201941%2C%20the%20warfighting%20concept%20of%20America%2C%20Britain%20and%20other%20Western%20nations%20has%20been%20to%20maintain%20relatively%20small%20armies%20backed%20by%20copious%20amounts%20of%20airpower.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-air-force-far-from-ready-for-mission-taiwan-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcept%3C%2Fa%3E%20eventually%20worked%20in%20World%20War%20II.%20It%20might%20have%20worked%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%20to%20repel%20a%20massive%20Soviet%20ground%20invasion%20of%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20air%20war%20over%20Ukraine%20raises%20doubts%20about%20this%20approach.%20If%20Ukrainian%20S-300%20and%20Patriot%20anti-aircraft%20missiles%20can%20destroy%20Russian%20planes%2C%20then%20couldn't%20Russian%20missiles%20do%20the%20same%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-teaching-nato-air-forces-lessons-fighting-russia-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENATO%20planes%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Ukraine%20claims%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwar.ukraine.ua%2Ffaq%2Fwhat-are-the-russian-death-toll-and-other-losses-in-ukraine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E369%20Russian%20warplanes%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20shot%20down%20as%20of%20February%202025%2C%20with%20most%20claimed%20by%20missiles%20rather%20than%20Ukraine's%20small%20fleet%20of%20fighter%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Western%20experts%20are%20paying%20close%20attention%20to%20how%20Russia%20has%20managed%20to%20make%20its%20air%20force%20relevant%20to%20the%20ground%20war.%20Much%20like%20the%20Russian%20war%20machine%20in%20general%2C%20the%20Russian%20air%20force%20is%20now%20emphasizing%20brute-force%20tactics%20that%20rely%20on%20massive%20amounts%20of%20bombs%20rather%20than%20accuracy.%20Instead%20of%20running%20the%20gauntlet%20of%20Ukrainian%20air%20defenses%20as%20they%20drop%20their%20bombs%2C%20Russian%20jets%20safely%20orbit%20up%20to%2060%20miles%20behind%20the%20Russian%20front%20line%20%E2%80%94%20out%20of%20range%20of%20Ukrainian%20long-range%20surface-to-air%20missiles%20%E2%80%94%20and%20lob%20glide%20bombs.%20These%20are%20low-budget%20guided%20weapons%20that%20mate%20a%20conventional%20iron%20bomb%20with%20a%20satellite-guidance%20system%2C%20and